# Calimingo Permit Tools — Cursor Rules
> Scoped to the permits module only. Does not affect existing app behavior.

---

## Module Boundaries

All permit code is self-contained. Never import from or write to existing app folders.

### This module owns:
- `app/permits/**`
- `app/api/permits/**`
- `components/permits/**`
- `lib/permits/**`
- `types/permits.ts`

### Shared files — extend carefully, never overwrite:
- `lib/db/schema.ts` — add new permit tables at the bottom only, under a `// PERMITS MODULE` comment
- `app/layout.tsx` — only touch to add the Permit Tools nav link

---

## AI Model

Always use `claude-sonnet-4-20250514` in all permit API routes.
Do not use any other model — other parts of the app use different models.

```ts
model: "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
max_tokens: 1000, // use 2000 only for redline-drafter and site-plan-generator
```

---

## Prompts

All Claude prompts live in `lib/permits/prompts.ts` only.
Never inline a prompt inside an API route file.

```ts
// ✅ Good
import { RENDERING_INTERPRETER_PROMPT } from "@/lib/permits/prompts"

// ❌ Bad
const prompt = `You are a permit technician...`
```

Always instruct Claude to return JSON only — no markdown, no preamble.
Always wrap `JSON.parse` in try/catch.

---

## API Routes

- All permit routes go under `app/api/permits/` only
- Every route must have try/catch
- Return consistent response shapes:

```ts
// Success
return NextResponse.json({ success: true, data: result })

// Error
return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: "Human readable message" }, { status: 500 })
```

- Validate all inputs — return 400 for missing required fields
- Never expose raw error messages or stack traces to the client

---

## Types

All permit types live in `types/permits.ts`.
Never redefine a type locally inside a component or route.

```ts
// ✅ Good
import type { DrawingAnalysisResult, RenderingInterpretation } from "@/types/permits"

// ❌ Bad
const result: { dimensions: any[] } = ...
```

No `any`. No `as unknown`. No `!` non-null assertions.

---

## Components

- Default to Server Components
- Add `"use client"` only when hooks or browser APIs are needed
- Keep components under ~150 lines — split if larger
- Tailwind classes only — no inline styles
- Always handle loading and error states explicitly

---

## File Uploads

- Drawing Analyzer: `image/jpeg`, `image/png`, `application/pdf`
- Site Plan Generator: `image/jpeg`, `image/png`, `application/pdf`
- PDF Assembler: `application/pdf` only
- Validate MIME type on both client and server
- Cap file size at 10MB client-side before upload

```ts
if (file.size > 10 * 1024 * 1024) {
  setError("File must be under 10MB")
  return
}
```

---

## Tool 7 — Specific Rules

### The Engineer Confirmation Gate
This is the most critical rule in the entire module.
The generate endpoint must NEVER proceed if any feature has `engineerConfirmed: false`.

```ts
// This check is REQUIRED in /api/permits/site-plan-generator/generate/route.ts
// Do not remove, skip, or work around it under any circumstances
const unconfirmed = inputs.confirmedFeatures.filter(f => !f.engineerConfirmed)
if (unconfirmed.length > 0) {
  return NextResponse.json(
    { success: false, error: "All features must be confirmed by the engineer before generating." },
    { status: 400 }
  )
}
```

Also enforced on the client — the Generate button must be disabled until all features
are confirmed or removed. Both client and server enforce this independently.

### SVG and DXF Are Pure Functions
`lib/permits/sitePlanSvg.ts` and `lib/permits/sitePlanDxf.ts` must:
- Never call the Claude API or any external service
- Never have side effects
- Be fully deterministic — same input always produces same output
- Be testable in complete isolation from the rest of the app

```ts
// ✅ Correct
export function generateSitePlanSvg(inputs: SitePlanInputs): string { ... }

// ❌ Wrong — no async, no API calls
export async function generateSitePlanSvg(inputs: SitePlanInputs): Promise<string> { ... }
```

### TBC for Missing Dimensions
SVG and DXF generators must show "TBC" for any unconfirmed or missing dimension.
Never render 0, null, or undefined as a dimension value.

```ts
// ✅ Correct
const width = confirmedDimensions[feature.id]?.width
const widthLabel = width != null ? `${width}ft` : "TBC"

// ❌ Wrong
const widthLabel = confirmedDimensions[feature.id]?.width ?? 0
```

### Unconfirmed Features Never Render
If `engineerConfirmed: false`, the feature must not appear in SVG or DXF output.
Filter before passing to generators — not inside the generators themselves.

### Disclaimer Is Non-Negotiable
Every output must include this text verbatim:
```
"AI-GENERATED DRAFT — FOR ENGINEER USE ONLY.
This document has not been reviewed or stamped by a licensed professional.
It must not be submitted for permitting or used for construction."
```
- SVG: diagonal watermark in light gray
- DXF: TEXT entity on DISCLAIMER layer
- Data sheet: bold banner top and bottom of every page

Never remove or make the disclaimer optional. Never hide it behind a toggle.

### State Management
Tool 7 page uses `useReducer` — not `useState`.
All stage transitions go through the reducer.
Never mutate state directly outside of dispatch calls.

### DXF Format
Always generate DXF R12 format for maximum CAD compatibility.
Do not use external DXF libraries — generate via string templates.
Always include all layers defined in the spec even if empty.

---

## AI Output Rules (All Tools)

Every AI-generated output must be:
- Editable by the engineer before use
- Clearly labeled as AI-generated
- Never auto-submitted or auto-applied

Confidence levels must always be visible for Drawing Analyzer and Tool 7 outputs.
Low-confidence items must be visually flagged (yellow/red).

